<HEADLINE>
FT  25 FEB 94 / UK Company News: Alliance Resources Dollars 0.38m in loss
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In its first set of results since reconstruction proposals were put to
shareholders last June, Alliance Resources, the oil and gas exploration and
production company, reported pre-tax losses of Dollars 381,000 (Pounds
261,000) for the six months to October 31. For the year to April 30 1993
there were losses of Dollars 1.63m.
The reduced deficit reflected a cut in administrative expenses to Dollars
407,000 (Dollars 1.54m for 12 months), a fall in net interest costs to
Dollars 62,000 (Dollars 198,000) and a small increase in production.
Turnover was Dollars 461,000 (Dollars 631,000). Losses per share were 0.01p
(0.09p).
The June proposals comprised the acquisition of Manx Petroleum, the
acquisition of a further 14.25 per cent in the Valentine field, a Pounds
2.8m rights issue and placing together with a capital reconstruction and the
appointment of two non-executive directors, Mr James Prior as chairman and
Lord Torrington.
In addition, the company's listing was restored in July and the
reorganisation plan for its Alliance Resources (USA) subsidiary was approved
by the US Bankruptcy Court.
Mr Prior said the changes did not have a material effect on the results.
</TEXT>
