<HEADLINE>
FT  25 FEB 94 / UK Company News: London Finance net assets rise
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Over the year ended December 31 net asset value per share of the London
Finance &amp; Investment Group, the investment finance and management concern,
expanded from 20p to 36.67p while pre-tax profits slipped from Pounds
226,000 to Pounds 192,000.
Earnings per share were 0.54p against 0.67p while the dividend is lifted to
0.5p (0.4p).
The pre-tax figure was after an exceptional charge of Pounds 31,000 (Pounds
345,000) being the cost of the warrant issue written off during 1993.
