<HEADLINE>
FT  25 FEB 94 / Letters to the Editor: Better to lock in directors with
options - or offer them a riskier route? (1)
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr D M BARCLAY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, While the position outlined by Mr C W Daws (Letters, February 22)
regarding share options is correct it overlooked another central point.
Share options, as well as rewarding directors, normally, by their structure,
tie them to a company for a number of years as it is usual to have a waiting
period before the option can be exercised.
A cash bonus scheme could only achieve this same aim if payment were
deferred for several years, perhaps on a 'rolling forward' basis.
D M Barclay,
Richardson Hosken International,
100 Fenchurch Street,
London EC3M 5LQ
</TEXT>
<XX>
