<HEADLINE>
FT  25 FEB 94 / Technology (Worth Watching): Fax designed for public use
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW FISHER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
For those who want to send a fax when at an airport, station, hotel or other
public place, the French company Schlumberger has developed a terminal which
accepts payment by plastic cards through an anti-vandal reader.
Publifax costs FFr47,000 (Pounds 5,460) and has a telephone handset for
voice communication. Schlumberger says it is the first to be
purpose-designed for public use. The user lays the document on the surface
at the bottom of the terminal. The scanner is several inches above, behind
protection. This ensures documents cannot be lost and minimises the
potential for vandalism. Schlumberger: France, 47 46 62 47
</TEXT>
