FT  25 FEB 94 / Cleared analyst returns to SFA
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Thorold Mackie, the Scottish investment analyst whose conviction for
insider dealing was quashed on appeal last week, has had his registration
with the Securities and Futures Authority restored.
The move, which was not automatic, followed a meeting of an SFA panel
yesterday which concluded that Mr Mackie was a 'fit and proper' person. The
decision means he can resume his full duties at stockbrokers Bell Lawrie
White. He voluntarily suspended his registration when he was first charged
two years ago.
