<HEADLINE>
FT  25 FEB 94 / Tumim calls for changes at Maze
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Improvements to Northern Ireland's top-security Maze jail complex were
recommended yesterday by Judge Stephen Tumim, the chief inspector of
prisons.
He made 76 recommendations in a report on the jail. Five proposals, relating
to security issues, were kept secret.
The report called for better conditions for inmates including access to
toilets at all times, more access to communal areas for education, craft and
hobbies, and arrangements to end the two periods a day when prisoners are
locked up in their cells.
Judge Tumim also said overtime worked by prison officers should be reduced
with a view to abolishing it.
