<HEADLINE>
FT  25 FEB 94 / French try to hook fish-eaters
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
France launched a FFr10m (Pounds 1.14m) campaign to persuade consumers to
eat more fish, a concession to fishermen who staged a violent strike earlier
this month. The campaign is partly funded by the European Union. Radio
advertisements depict French fishermen as unsung heroes, bringing home the
fish after a night at sea. EU and other trading partners have accused France
of bending international trade rules by imposing lengthy border checks,
stringent veterinary controls and minimum prices on imported fish.
</TEXT>
