FT  24 FEB 94 / International Company News: Black &amp; Decker margins to rise
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Black &amp; Decker, the US power tools group, expects higher margins during
1994, due to lower costs and new product introductions, but said the gains
would be confined to the US, Reuter reports.
'We do not anticipate significant improvement in European consumer or
industrial markets during 1994,' said Mr Nolan Archibald, chairman and chief
execu-tive.
