<HEADLINE>
FT  24 FEB 94 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
We are promised Britt Ekland, Lulu, Adrian Edmondson, Helen Lederer, Jo
Brand and Zandra Rhodes all 'guesting' in Absolutely Fabulous. Can this
really be a good idea? The opening episode of this series packed in a
similar roster of star names, and turned out to be the least funny episode
of the lot (9.35 BBC1). A newer and more conventional comedy, Nelson's
Column, stars John Gordon Sinclair, the eternal juvenile lead from Gregory's
Girl, as a lovelorn (well, randy) local newspaper reporter (8.00 BBC1).
BBC2 begins a three-part series, In Search Of Our Ancestors, with
anthropologist Donald Johanson returning to Ethiopia to re-tell the story of
the 'missing link' (9.30 BBC2). Commando relies on the same exultation in
military macho that used to sell 'Battle' comics to schoolboys in the 1950s.
Tough chaps face fearful challenges and are driven to the limits of
endurance (9.30 ITV).
Will Late Picasso complete BBC2's Picasso season by facing up to the public
contempt for the Modern movement? (11.15 BBC2).
</TEXT>
