<HEADLINE>
FT  24 FEB 94 / TUC sets up new governing structure
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR, Labour Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The biggest internal shake-up of the Trades Union Congress for 73 years was
agreed yesterday by senior union leaders in spite of reservations about the
speed of the proposed changes from the TGWU general union.
The reforms, being carried through by Mr John Monks, TUC general secretary,
involve making the organisation more of a campaigning body.
All of its 17 committees are to be abolished and replaced by a governing
executive board. A new department is to be established for campaign and
lobbying activities. The general council is to meet about five times a year
instead of monthly.
The TUC is planning the 'relaunch' for March 1. A number of events and
conferences are to be held in the next few months on issues such as
unemployment and inner-city deprivation.
</TEXT>
